							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">With all due respect Dretch... if they didn't raise the level cap... everyone would be lvl 50... and all lvl 50 zones would be wiped clean of nameds every 10 seconds.
<br />

<br />
part of a MMORPG is moving "up and out" of zones and into new ones so that crowdation isn't an issue...
<br />

<br />
Also... if I sit much longer at lvl 50 killing the same stuff I'll go nuts... we need to move forward... AA's after 7-8 mths of being max level simply will not cut it.... a while back it would have worked fine... but I have killed some epic 24-man raid mobs 40+ times... can you say BORING?
<br />

<br />
You should be able to have fun as a casual gamer without comparing yourself the "the hardcore"... where as "hardcore" people can not have fun if the casual gamer and him are the same level and strength... no after 2 weeks would the casual gamer like it because there would be nothing left to work towards.
<br />

<br />
There is a very delicate balance here... and allowing casual gamers to accomplish the same goals as hard core players will not keep anyone happy for more than a couple weeks.
<br />

<br />
I am not saying the whole focus of the game should be on "the hardcore" but what I am saying is you should be happy with who YOU are... not what you look like when standing next to the other guys.
<br />

<br />
That's kind of like saying body builders should be limited on the amount of muscle mass they can obtain because you feel uncomfortable in singles bars <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />  people make choices... I for one am not a body builder... I do not wish to be... and therefore I don't care what they look like... if you had a similar outlook towards the game you would be a happier person.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.thedauntless.org" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://tinyurl.com/6qjqw/blah.png" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
